The paper discusses the generation of user profiles based on topics of expertise or interest, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of Wikipedia category graph, which falls under the subfield of semantic web (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the usability of the generated profiles, which can be related to human-computer interaction (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SD).
